content:
Create a report to see how many and which specific external documents are being attached to cases. Use this information to see which external sources have the most impact on closing cases. This report is helpful when you have set up Salesforce Federated Search, which gives users access to external search results when using the Knowledge One Widget.

Required editions: Essentials and Unlimited Edition with Service Cloud.
Professional, Enterprise, Performance, and Developer Editions are available for an additional cost.

User permissions needed:
- Manage Custom Report Types
- Run Reports
- Create and Customize Reports

To create a custom report type, select Cases as the primary object, enter a label and description, and select the Other Reports category. Define the report records set by relating another object and creating an A to B relationship with External Documents.

To run the report, click New Report, select Cases with External Documents, drag and drop Case ID, Case Number, Display URL, Title fields onto the report, and save it.
title: Create a Custom Report on External Documents Attached to Cases in Salesforce
keywords: Case Deflection from Discussions and Articles
